key.description: Unique identifier for the game, includes the title and developer in brackets.

status.description: Current development status of the game (e.g., Abandoned, Completed, Ongoing, Onhold).

url.description: Direct link to the game’s thread or page on the source site.

bayesian_rating.description: Normalized rating of the game using a Bayesian average to account for varying number of reviews.

site_rating.description: Average rating given on the original site.

site_rating_count.description: Number of ratings submitted on the site.

play_time_hours.description: Estimated time to play the game, in hours.

engine.description: The game engine used (e.g., Ren’Py, Unity).

site_std_version.description: Standardized version format derived from the site’s version number.

site_version.description: The version string as listed on the site.

site_last_update_date.description: Date when the game was last updated on the site.

site_release_date.description: Original release date of the game.

developer.description: Name of the game’s developer or team.

platforms.description: Platforms supported by the game (e.g., Windows, Mac, Linux, Android).

is_vn.description: Boolean flag indicating whether the game is a visual novel (True/False).

censored.description: Boolean flag indicating whether the game is censored (True/False).
